  <info>## WHAT IS IT?

Modeling tumor growth with adaptive therapy

## HOW IT WORKS

Creates sensitive and resistant clone with given number of cells. The cancer cells grow with the availability of resources and starvation time. The drug can be added into the environment metronomically, adaptively, or manually with a button.

## HOW TO USE IT

Click on Setup to erase the world and create a new world with given number of cell-counts.
Click on go to run the model (Press this button again to Stop)
Click on step-go to run the model tick by tick
Click on BOLUS to manually add drug


## THINGS TO NOTICE

Note the growth represented in the adjoining graph. The plot reports the following
 - Resistant cell count (orange line)
 - Sensitive cell count (black line)
 - Number of resources  (green line) and 
 - Number of drug molecules (blue line)


## THINGS TO TRY

- Run with out any drugs in the environment.
- Run with drugs given periodically.
- Run the adaptive therapy

## EXTENDING THE MODEL



## NETLOGO FEATURES


## RELATED MODELS



## CREDITS AND REFERENCES

- https://github.com/ishworthapa/adaptive-therapy-modeling</info>
